          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-13 12:38:14" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(figurative extension of meaning of {L:κοιλία&lt;SDBG:κοιλία:000000&gt;}[a] ‘belly,’ {D:8.67}) the psychological faculty of desire, intent, and feeling{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>heart</Gloss>
                <Gloss>feelings</Gloss>
                <Gloss>desires</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though some persons have attempted to distinguish between {L:σπλάγχνον&lt;SDBG:σπλάγχνον:000001&gt;}[b], κοιλία[c], and {L:νεφρός&lt;SDBG:νεφρός:000000&gt;}, it is extremely doubtful whether this is really possible or practical. The semantic focus in the use of these terms is clearly the deeper and more intimate feelings and emotions. In some languages one can use a term which literally means ‘belly’ or ‘bowels,’ but more often than not, these emotions are associated with some particular organ of the body such as heart, spleen, liver, etc. Rather, however, than attempting to employ a figurative expression which may or may not be fully equivalent, it is often preferable to refer to the emotional content by using terms such as ‘feelings,’ ‘intents,’ ‘desires,’ or ‘compassion,’ depending upon the context.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
